<bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Biography</head>
	<p><persname>Alison Paul</persname>, an author and illustrator of children's books, grew up in <geogname>California</geogname> before moving to <geogname>New England</geogname>.  She attended the <corpname>Rhode Island School of Design</corpname> and is the author of two books, <title render="italic">The Crow</title> (2007) and <title render="italic">Sunday Love</title> (2010). [http://alisonpaulart.com/]</p>
<note><p>      <emph render="bold">Published Works:</emph></p>
<list type="simple">
<item><bibref><title render="italic">The Crow</title>, <imprint>Boston: <publisher>Houghton Mifflin</publisher>, <date type="publication">2007</date>.</imprint></bibref></item>
<item><bibref><title render="italic">Sunday love</title>, <imprint>Boston: <publisher>Houghton Mifflin</publisher>, <date type="publication">2010</date>.</imprint></bibref></item></list></note>
<p></p>
<p></p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>The collection contains galley proofs of <title render="italic">The Crow</title> published in 2007.</p>
</scopecontent>

